			<td><b>Editor and Associate Publisher,&nbsp;<I>Mobile Electronics</I></b></td>
		</tr>
		
		
		<tr>
			<td><br><img src=/shared_files/techspeakers_photos/Daniels_Solomon.jpg align=left valign="top">&nbsp;Solomon Daniels has been Editor and Associate Publisher of Mobile Electronics Magazine for more than eight years. A former mobile electronics installer and salesperson, Daniels has worked in all facets of the industry, including retail, manufacturing, technical support, marketing and product development. His most recent position was as National Marketing Manager for Code-Alarm Inc. (now named Code Systems, a subsidiary of Audiovox Corporation). Daniels has been active in the Consumer Electronics industry, serving as judge for CES Innovations and as moderator for key seminars on several occasions. He also is active as an advisor to MERA (Mobile Enhancement Retailers Association) and oversees the annual selection process for the Top 100 Installers, Top 50 Retailers, Installer of the Year and Retailer of the Year awards, given out by the magazine.</td>
		
		
